    en: "New York is a no-fault state. After a car crash, the injured person's own insurance (or the insurance on the car they were riding in) pays for medical bills and lost wages, no matter who caused the crash. Pain-and-suffering claims against the other driver are only allowed if the injury meets the 'serious injury' test in Insurance Law 5102(d). A no-fault claim form (NF-2) must be filed within 30 days. A DMV accident report (MV-104) is filed within 10 days when anyone is hurt or when property damage is high. Knowing these rules helps an injured person avoid costly mistakes in the first weeks after a crash."
